---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Wine Guardian Repair | Southern California | Cellar Cooling Systems";
const description = "Wine Guardian repair across Southern California, ducted split, ductless self-contained, through-the-wall cellar cooling. Walk-in wine cellar climate control. $89 residential / $120 commercial diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/wine-guardian-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Wine Guardian a wine cooler or something different?",
    a: "Different category. <b>Wine Guardian</b> manufactures <b>wine cellar cooling systems</b>, climate-control HVAC equipment installed to refrigerate walk-in wine cellars, custom wine rooms, and storage closets converted to wine storage. These are not wine coolers (the freestanding or built-in cabinet appliances like Sub-Zero, Viking, Liebherr that hold 24-200 bottles). Wine Guardian systems serve cellar volumes from 200 cu ft small closet conversions up to 5,000+ cu ft commercial cellars + restaurant + hotel installations. The product is mechanical cooling equipment with refrigeration components (compressor, condenser, evaporator coil, refrigerant lines, expansion valve) sized + tuned for wine-storage temperature + humidity targets, typically 55-58°F at 55-65% relative humidity. For wine cooler appliance service, see our <a href='/services/wine-cooler-repair/'>wine cooler repair hub</a>; for cellar cooling-system service like Wine Guardian, you're on the right page."
  },
  {
    q: "What types of Wine Guardian systems does our LA service cover?",
    a: "Three system architectures cover most LA Wine Guardian installations. (1) <b>Ducted split systems</b> (DSXi Series + Sentinel Split), separate evaporator + condenser units connected by refrigerant + electrical lines, evaporator inside the cellar with ductwork distributing cooling, condenser outside the cellar (often outdoors or in mechanical room). Most common in custom-home walk-in cellars where the cellar is integrated into the architecture. (2) <b>Ductless self-contained</b> (Sentinel Series ductless), single unit installed into a hole through the cellar wall, evaporator + condenser in one chassis, no ductwork. Common in retrofit conversions where running ducts wasn't feasible. (3) <b>Through-the-wall units</b>, mounted directly through the cellar wall like an air conditioner, condenser exhausting to the adjacent room or exterior. Common in basement-converted cellars + garage cellars. Each architecture has its own service approach + parts inventory."
  },
  {
    q: "Wine cellar reaching too warm, what's the diagnostic path?",
    a: "Cellar temperature rising above the 55-58°F target is the most common Wine Guardian service call. Diagnostic order: (1) <b>Condenser airflow + cleanliness</b>, restricted condenser airflow (dust accumulation, blocked exhaust, condenser fan failure) prevents heat rejection. Free if cleaning resolves; condenser fan motor $295-$425. (2) <b>Refrigerant charge</b>, slow R-410A leak at flare fittings on split systems is the #1 long-term Wine Guardian failure. Leak detection + flare-fitting reseal + recharge $385-$685 depending on leak severity + lines accessibility. EPA-certified refrigerant handling required. (3) <b>Compressor</b>, high run-current or no-start indicates compressor failure. Compressor replacement $785-$1,485 depending on system size + accessibility. (4) <b>Evaporator coil freeze-up</b>, counter-intuitively, frozen evap coil reduces cooling delivery. Caused by low refrigerant, low airflow, or thermostat malfunction. Defrost + diagnose root cause $245-$385. (5) <b>Thermostat drift</b>, Wine Guardian thermostats drift over 8-12 years, $185-$285 replacement. We carry leak-detection equipment + EPA refrigerant license on dispatch."
  },
  {
    q: "Humidity is wrong in our wine cellar, too dry or too wet?",
    a: "Wine Guardian premium systems include integrated humidity control to hold cellars at the 55-65% RH target wine storage requires. Humidity issues split into two patterns. <b>Too dry (humidity below 50% RH)</b>: humidification system failed or empty water reservoir; reservoir refill is owner-side maintenance, humidifier solenoid valve replacement $245-$345, humidifier pad/element $185-$275. Common in LA dry-summer months. <b>Too wet (condensation forming, humidity above 70% RH)</b>: drain line clogged (preventing condensate evacuation, water backing up + recirculating), $145-$215 drain clearing service; or drain pump failed on systems with active drain pumps, $285-$385. Both conditions damage wine corks + labels over time, corks dry + shrink in low humidity (allowing oxidation), corks mold + labels lift in high humidity. We service the humidity control as carefully as the temperature control because both matter for wine preservation."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Wine Guardian repair cost in LA?",
    a: "<b>Residential diagnostic $89</b>, waived with repair. <b>Commercial diagnostic $120</b> for restaurant + hotel + retail wine cellars (commercial dispatch + business-hours scheduling). Common service bands: condenser fan motor $295-$425; condenser cleaning + tune-up service $185 flat; refrigerant leak detection + flare-fitting reseal + recharge $385-$685; compressor replacement $785-$1,485 (size + accessibility dependent); evaporator coil clean + defrost + root-cause $245-$385; thermostat replacement $185-$285; humidifier solenoid valve $245-$345; humidifier pad/element $185-$275; drain line clearing $145-$215; drain pump replacement $285-$385; expansion valve $345-$485; refrigerant line repair $385-$685 depending on accessibility. Annual preventive maintenance service $245-$385 (includes condenser clean, refrigerant level check, electrical connection inspection, drain line clearing, thermostat verification), recommended for residential cellars over 500 cu ft + all commercial cellars."
  },
  {
    q: "Does Wine Guardian service require special certifications?",
    a: "Yes, <b>EPA Section 608 refrigerant certification</b> is required for any work that disturbs the refrigerant circuit (leak detection + repair, recharge, compressor replacement, refrigerant line work). Wine Guardian systems use R-410A refrigerant on current-generation units; older units may use R-22 (phased out, parts increasingly scarce, often economical replacement-vs-repair territory). Our LA service technicians carry EPA 608 Universal certification (#1346255700410). <b>HVAC contractor license</b> applies for systems treated as HVAC equipment (most large ducted split + commercial Wine Guardian installations). We hold an active California CSLB C-20 HVAC license plus BHGS appliance-repair registration #A49573. Certifications matter for liability + insurance reasons + because environmental refrigerant regulations have real penalties for non-compliant handling. Independent service without EPA Section 608 cannot legally perform refrigerant work, they're limited to electrical + mechanical service that doesn't disturb the refrigerant circuit. Confirm certification status when comparing service quotes."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Wine Guardian Cellar Cooling Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Wine Guardian Wine Cellar Cooling Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Wine Guardian wine cellar cooling system repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. ducted split (DSXi + Sentinel Split), ductless self-contained, through-the-wall units. Walk-in residential + commercial wine cellar climate control. EPA Section 608 certified refrigerant work. CSLB licensed HVAC contractor. $89 residential / $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair on residential.",
    "offers": [
      { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } },
      { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "120.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Commercial diagnostic fee" } }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Wine Guardian Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Wine Guardian cellar cooling service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Wine Guardian Repair</div>
    <h1>Wine Guardian Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Wine Guardian is the specialty wine cellar cooling brand whose systems hold walk-in wine cellars + custom wine rooms at the 55-58°F + 55-65% relative humidity targets that wine preservation requires. <b>This is a different product category from wine cooler appliances</b>, Wine Guardian builds the climate-control HVAC equipment that refrigerates wine rooms, not the freestanding cabinets that hold individual bottles. Our LA Wine Guardian service covers the full system architecture lineup: <b>ducted split systems</b> (DSXi Series + Sentinel Split for custom-home walk-in cellars), <b>ductless self-contained</b> (Sentinel Series for retrofit conversions), and <b>through-the-wall units</b> (basement + garage cellar conversions). We hold EPA 608 Universal refrigerant certification (#1346255700410), an active California CSLB C-20 HVAC contractor license, plus BHGS #A49573 appliance-repair registration, credentials required for legal Wine Guardian service. Same-day dispatch across LA, Orange County, Ventura County. <b>Residential diagnostic $89 (waived with repair); commercial diagnostic $120</b> for restaurant + hotel + retail cellars.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Cellar cooling systems</b>, not wine cooler appliances (separate category)</li>
      <li><b>EPA Section 608 + CSLB licensed</b>, required for refrigerant work</li>
      <li><b>3 system architectures</b>, ducted split, ductless, through-the-wall</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential / $120 commercial diagnostic</b></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · EPA 608 Certified</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>$89 residential · $120 commercial</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Wine Guardian in LA, luxury cellar cooling, EPA-regulated refrigerant work</h2>
    <p>Wine Guardian's LA install base concentrates in luxury custom-home walk-in cellars + restaurant + hotel commercial cellars. Custom-home installations: Bel Air + Beverly Hills + Holmby Hills + Pacific Palisades estates with dedicated wine rooms 200-2,000 cu ft, cellar storage commonly 500-2,500 bottles, ducted split systems matched to architectural integration. Commercial installations: West LA + Beverly Hills + DTLA + WeHo restaurants with reach-in display cellars + back-of-house storage cellars, hotel sommelier programs at high-end properties, retail wine merchants with climate-controlled display + storage. Each install context has its own service expectations + dispatch logistics.</p>
    <p>Service for Wine Guardian + peer brands (Whisperkool, Breezaire, CellarPro, Vinotemp commercial cooling) is fundamentally HVAC service, refrigerant circuits, EPA-regulated work, compressor + condenser + evaporator + expansion valve diagnostics. Our LA Wine Guardian service runs through factory-trained technicians with EPA Section 608 Universal certification, California CSLB license, and the leak-detection + recovery equipment + refrigerant supply that legal refrigerant work requires. Independent service without these credentials can't legally perform refrigerant work, they're limited to electrical + thermostat + drain-line service. We carry full credentials so we can complete the job rather than partial-service-and-refer.</p>
    <p>Wine Guardian is currently owned by Air Innovations / Senasys Inc (NY-based since the brand's 2014 transition). Manufacturing remains in New York; US parts distribution serves LA at typical 3-7 day lead on common components (condenser fan motors, thermostats, humidifier valves, drain pumps); compressor + specialty refrigeration parts at 5-10 day lead. We carry common parts on dispatch for same-day completion when initial diagnostic identifies common failure patterns.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Wine Guardian failures our LA techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Refrigerant leak at flare fittings (split systems #1)</h3><p>Slow R-410A leak at line-set flare connections is the most common long-term Wine Guardian failure. Leak detection + flare reseal + recharge $385-$685. EPA Section 608 work, must be performed by certified technician.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Condenser fan motor + condenser cleaning</h3><p>Restricted airflow + dust accumulation + fan motor failure prevent heat rejection. Cleaning service $185 flat. Fan motor $295-$425.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Compressor failure (8-15 year typical)</h3><p>High run-current or no-start. Compressor replacement $785-$1,485 depending on system size + accessibility. Always verify root cause (electrical short, refrigerant flood-back, lubrication failure) before replacement.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Evaporator coil freeze-up</h3><p>Counter-intuitive symptom, frozen evap coil reduces cellar cooling delivery. Caused by low refrigerant, low airflow, or thermostat malfunction. Defrost + diagnose root cause $245-$385.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Humidity issues (drain line + humidifier)</h3><p>Too dry → humidifier solenoid valve $245-$345 or pad/element $185-$275. Too wet → drain line clearing $145-$215 or drain pump $285-$385. Both damage wine over time.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Thermostat drift (8-12 year pattern)</h3><p>Wine Guardian thermostats drift over time, cellar temp deviates from 55-58°F target without code throwing. Replacement $185-$285. Real-time temperature verification at diagnostic.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Wine Guardian system architectures we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>DSXi Series ducted split (high-capacity)</h3><p>High-capacity ducted split systems for large custom-home + commercial cellars. Evaporator inside cellar + condenser outdoors or in mechanical room, refrigerant lines + ductwork connecting. Most common LA luxury-home Wine Guardian.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Sentinel Split (mid-capacity ducted)</h3><p>Mid-capacity ducted split for standard custom-home walk-in cellars 300-1,200 cu ft. Same architecture as DSXi at lower capacity + price tier.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Sentinel Series ductless self-contained</h3><p>Single-unit ductless installed through cellar wall opening. Evaporator + condenser in one chassis, no ductwork required. Common in retrofit cellar conversions.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Through-the-wall units</h3><p>Mounted directly through cellar wall like an air conditioner, condenser exhausting to adjacent room or exterior. Common in basement-converted + garage cellars.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Humidity control systems</h3><p>Integrated humidification on premium Wine Guardian models maintains 55-65% RH. Humidifier solenoid valve + pad/element + water reservoir all serviceable separately.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Annual preventive maintenance</h3><p>$245-$385 service includes condenser clean, refrigerant level check, electrical connection inspection, drain line clearing, thermostat verification. Recommended for residential cellars 500+ cu ft + all commercial cellars.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Wine Guardian repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Residential diagnostic</b></td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Commercial diagnostic</b></td><td>$120</td><td>Restaurant / hotel / retail</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Condenser cleaning + tune-up</td><td>$185 flat</td><td>Restricted airflow restoration</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Condenser fan motor</td><td>$295 – $425</td><td>Heat-rejection failure</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Refrigerant leak detection + reseal + recharge</td><td>$385 – $685</td><td>EPA 608 required</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Compressor replacement (size-dependent)</td><td>$785 – $1,485</td><td>8-15 year typical service life</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Evaporator coil defrost + diagnose</td><td>$245 – $385</td><td>Freeze-up root cause</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Expansion valve</td><td>$345 – $485</td><td>Flow restriction symptom</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Refrigerant line repair</td><td>$385 – $685</td><td>Accessibility-dependent</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermostat replacement</td><td>$185 – $285</td><td>8-12 year drift pattern</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Humidifier solenoid valve</td><td>$245 – $345</td><td>Too-dry symptom</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Humidifier pad / element</td><td>$185 – $275</td><td>Humidification failure</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drain line clearing</td><td>$145 – $215</td><td>Too-wet humidity symptom</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drain pump replacement</td><td>$285 – $385</td><td>Active-drain systems</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Annual preventive maintenance</td><td>$245 – $385</td><td>Cellars 500+ cu ft + all commercial</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Pricing reflects EPA Section 608 + CSLB licensed refrigerant work. Independent service without these credentials cannot legally perform refrigerant repairs. Older R-22 systems (pre-2010) often face parts-availability constraints + replacement-vs-repair economic decisions.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LA service areas, Wine Guardian cellar cooling concentrations</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Custom-home luxury cellars</h4><p>Bel Air · <a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Holmby Hills · Pacific Palisades · Brentwood · <a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a></p></div>
      <div><h4>Hancock Park + Mid-Wilshire historic</h4><p>Hancock Park · Windsor Square · Mid-Wilshire · Fremont Place</p></div>
      <div><h4>Pasadena + San Marino estates</h4><p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · La Cañada Flintridge · Arcadia</p></div>
      <div><h4>Restaurant + hotel commercial</h4><p>West LA + Beverly Hills + DTLA + <a href="/west-hollywood/">WeHo</a> sommelier programs + restaurant cellars</p></div>
      <div><h4>Conejo + Ventura County</h4><p><a href="/thousand-oaks/">Thousand Oaks</a> · Westlake Village · Calabasas · Hidden Hills</p></div>
      <div><h4>OC luxury coastal</h4><p>Newport Coast · Corona del Mar · Crystal Cove · Laguna Beach · <a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a></p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related wine cooling + cellar service pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/services/wine-cellar-repair/">Wine cellar repair service hub →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/wine-cooler-repair/">Wine cooler repair service hub →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/sub-zero-wine-cooler-repair/">Sub-Zero wine cooler (cabinet appliance) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-wine-cooler-repair/">Viking wine cooler (cabinet appliance) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/liebherr-wine-cooler-repair/">Liebherr wine cooler (cabinet appliance) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/u-line-wine-cooler-repair/">U-Line wine cooler (cabinet appliance) →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Wine Guardian repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Wine Guardian service? Call the branch closest to your cellar.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance + HVAC service in LA, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential $89 (waived with repair); commercial $120. EPA Section 608 + CSLB licensed.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .model-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .model-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .section.alt .model-card { background: #fff; }
  .fail-block { background: #fff; border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px 22px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
